MODE <nick> <+|-><modes>

User modes: (* designates that the umode is oper only)

     USER MODE    DESCRIPTION
-----------------------------------------------------------------
       * a     - Is marked as a server admin in stats o/p.
         C     - Blocks CTCP requests (not including ACTION)
         D     - "Deaf": don't receive channel messages.
       * F     - Can see remote client connection/quit notices.
         g     - "Caller ID" mode: only allow accepted clients to message you.
         G     - "Soft Caller ID": only allow accepted clients and clients
                 on common channels to message you.
       * h     - Can see WHOIS notices.
       * H     - Operator status is hidden to other users.
         i     - Designates this client as 'invisible'.
         I     - Block /INVITE messages.
       * l     - Can see oper locops (local wallops).
       * N     - Designates this client as a network admin.
       * o     - Designates this client as an IRC Operator.
                 Use the OPER command to attain this.
         p     - Hides channel list in WHOIS.
         q     - Hides idle and signon time in WHOIS.
         r     - User has identified with services.
                 This mode can only be set by servers.
         R     - Only allow registered clients to message you.
         s     - Can see generic server messages and oper kills.
         S     - Client is connected via SSL/TLS.
         w     - Can see server wallops.
         W     - User is connected using a webirc gateway.
         x     - User's host has been spoofed by services.
                 This mode can only be set by servers and services.
       * y     - Can see stats/links/admin requests, etc.
       * z     - Can receive operwalls.
